        "subject": "LU-19874 misc: update module_init calls",
        "message": "LU-19874 misc: update module_init calls\n\n... to use late_initcall() for LNet and late_initcall_sync()\nfor services dependent on LNet. Both LNet and Lustre need\nnetworking to be available. So we use late_initcall_*().\nAnd LNet must be started for Lustre - hence late_initcall_sync()\nis used for Lustre to ensure that the LNet initialization has\nbeen completed.\n\nWhen Lustre is build as a module, these all evaluate to\nmodule_init() regardless. So nothing changes in the typical\ncase.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Timothy Day <timday@amazon.com>\nChange-Id: If0310f66c0a0192adacd21bbf36214446ca9316f\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64456\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
